<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
  <title>Bugbot</title>
  <link rel="icon" type="image/x-icon" href="https://s3-us-west-1.amazonaws.com/bugbot/favicon.ico">
  <style>
  <!-- build:include ../css/styles.min.css -->
  <!-- /build -->
  </style>
</head>
<body>

  <% if (ok) { %>

    <% if (msg.length) { %>

      <section class="notify">
        <span class="excite">Hooray!</span> &nbsp; You've installed Bugbot on your team's Slack &nbsp; <a class="anchor" href="#getting-started">Go to the next step</a>
      </section>

    <% } %>

  <% } else { %>

    <section class="notify">
      <span class="bummer">Well shoot.</span> &nbsp; Something got messed up. Please try removing Bugbot from your Slack integrations and try again.
    </section>

  <% } %>


  <header class="header">
    <div class="header-contents">
      <div class="bugbot-icon">
        <!-- build:include ../img/bugbot_icon.svg -->
        <!-- /build -->
      </div>
      <div class="bugbot-logo">
        <!-- build:include ../img/bugbot_logo.svg -->
        <!-- /build -->
      </div>
      <p class="bugbot-tag">
        Finally, your GitHub Issues in Slack!
      </p>
      <a
        class="slack-link"
        href="https://slack.com/oauth/authorize?scope=<%- scope %>&client_id=<%- client_id %>"
        >
        <!-- build:include ../img/addtoslackbutton.svg -->
        <!-- /build -->
      </a>
    </div>
  </header>

  <section class="content">
    <div class="row row-content between reverse">
      <div class="row-item">
        <h1 class="heading">
          Work out your issues in Slack
        </h1>
        <p class="content-text">
         Switching out of Slack to do a basic thing — like manage our GitHub Issues — was driving us crazy. So we made Bugbot! Just install it once for your Slack team, and everyone on it can access and create new issues from their GitHub accounts. Just like that.
       </p>
      </div>
      <div class="row-item">
        <!-- build:include ../img/slackwindow.svg -->
        <!-- /build -->
      </div>
    </div>
    <h1 class="heading">
      Getting Started
    </h1>
    <div class="row row-content between">
      <div class="row-item">
        <a id="getting-started"></a>
        <h2 class="sub-heading">
          Step 1 - Add to Slack
        </h2>
        <p class="content-text">
          Okay, this part is easy! Just hit the Add to Slack button and walk through Slack’s steps for installation.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="row-item">
        <div class="sparks-container">
          <div class="sparks">
            <!-- build:include ../img/buttonsparks.svg -->
            <!-- /build -->
          </div>
          <div class="sparks-button">
            <a
              class="slack-link"
              href="https://slack.com/oauth/authorize?scope=<%- scope %>&client_id=<%- client_id %>"
              >
              <!-- build:include ../img/addtoslackbutton-nope.svg -->
              <!-- /build -->
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="row row-content between reverse">
      <div class="row-item">
        <h2 class="sub-heading">
          Step 2 - Tell Your Team
        </h2>
        <p class="content-text">
          Once you’ve got Bugbot integrated with Slack, let your team know! (We recommend sending an alert with the <span class="code"> @channel</span> command in an announcements room, if you have one.)
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="row-item">
        <!-- build:include ../img/screenshot_tellteam.svg -->
        <!-- /build -->
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="row row-content between">
      <div class="row-item">
        <h2 class="sub-heading">
          Step 3 - Authenticate with GitHub
        </h2>
        <p class="content-text">
          Anyone who wants to use Bugbot will need to register their GitHub account, which is super easy. Just run <span class="code">/bugbot</span> to get authenticated.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="row-item">
        <!-- build:include ../img/github_logo.svg -->
        <!-- /build -->
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="row row-content between reverse">
      <div class="row-item">
        <h2 class="sub-heading">
          Step 4 - Set your repo
        </h2>
        <p class="content-text">
          Bugbot is super flexible, so everyone can be reading and writing to different GitHub repos. Run <span class="code">/bugbot repos</span> to find the repo you want to use, then run <span class="code">/bugbot repo org/reponame</span> to set it.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="row-item">
        <!-- build:include ../img/screenshot_configurerepo.svg -->
        <!-- /build -->
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="row row-content between">
      <div class="row-item">
        <h2 class="sub-heading">
          Then - Create Github Issues in Slack!
        </h2>
        <p class="content-text">
          Gone are the days of leaving Slack to create a new GitHub Issue. Just run <span class="code">/bugbot add [your issue name]</span> to create a new issue!
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="row-item">
        <!-- build:include ../img/screenshot_newissue.svg -->
        <!-- /build -->
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="row row-content between reverse">
      <div class="row-item">
        <h2 class="sub-heading">
          And then - Keep an eye on your Issues
        </h2>
        <p class="content-text">
          Your Github Issues are now available in Slack, too. Run <span class="code">/bugbot issues</span> to see all the latest.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="row-item">
        <!-- build:include ../img/screenshot_issuelist.svg -->
        <!-- /build -->
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="updates">
    <div class="updates-contents">
      <h1 class="updates-heading">
        We're just getting started!
      </h1>
      <p class="updates-message">
        Bugbot is made by <a class="inline-anchor" href="https://smallwins.today">Small Wins</a>, and we’ve got some really great things coming. Drop your email in here, we can’t wait to tell you more about what we’re working on!
    </p>
      <form class="form" action="/email" method="POST">
        <label for="email" class="label">
          <input class="input" type="email" name="email" placeholder="Here's my email">
          <button class="button">
            Thanks!
          </button>
        </label>
      </form>
      <p class="worries">
        Oh and don’t worry, this whole thing has a 0% forecast of spam. &#128588;
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="open-source">
    <div class="open-source-contents">
      <h1 class="open-source-heading">
        More projects by Small Wins
      </h1>

      <div class="row around">
        <div class="row-item">
          <a class="card" href="https://github.com/smallwins/bugbot">
            <div class="open-source-icon">
              <!-- build:include ../img/lumberjack_bugbot.svg -->
              <!-- /build -->
            </div>
            <h1 class="card-heading bugbot-heading">
              Bugbot on GitHub
            </h1>
            <p class="card-body">
              Add a feature — or run your own instance. Bugbot is fully open source!
            </p>
          </a>
        </div>
        <div class="row-item">
          <a class="card" href="https://github.com/smallwins/slack-express">
            <div class="open-source-icon">
              <!-- build:include ../img/lumberjack_se.svg -->
              <!-- /build -->
            </div>
            <h1 class="card-heading slack-express-heading">
              Slack Express
            </h1>
            <p class="card-body">
              Quickly implement Slack slash commands as Express middleware.
            </p>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="row around">
        <div class="row-item">
          <a class="card" href="https://github.com/smallwins/slack">
            <div class="open-source-icon">
              <!-- build:include ../img/lumberjack_slackjs.svg -->
              <!-- /build -->
            </div>
            <h1 class="card-heading slack-js-heading">
              JS Slack API client
            </h1>
            <p class="card-body">
              Slack API client written in ES2015 JavaScript
            </p>
          </a>
        </div>
        <div class="row-item">
          <a class="card" href="https://github.com/smallwins/slack-ui-template">
            <div class="open-source-icon">
              <!-- build:include ../img/lumberjack_slacksketch.svg -->
              <!-- /build -->
            </div>
            <h1 class="card-heading slack-ui-heading">
              Slack UI template
            </h1>
            <p class="card-body">
              Create rapid Sketch mock-ups of your Slack interactions.
            </p>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <footer class="footer">
    <div class="footer-contents">
      <div class="auto loves">
      <!-- build:include ../img/pencilpapercat.svg -->
      <!-- /build -->
      </div>
      <div class="auto bold">
        © small wins
      </div>
      <div>
        <a class="inline-anchor" href="https://github.com/smallwins/bugbot/wiki/Bugbot-Privacy-Policy">privacy policy</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </footer>

</body>
</html>

